Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Grease and flour one 10 inch tube pan. Combine oil, butter or margarine, and sugar together. Beat well with a mixer. Add eggs, flour, baking soda, salt, and vanilla; mix well. Stir in apples, coconut, raisins, and walnuts. Pour batter in prepared pan. Bake for 90 minutes. Remove cake from oven. Let it cool in the pan for a few minutes, and then remove from pan. If desired, make glaze. In a small saucepan, heat brown sugar, butter or margarine, and milk. Bring mixture to boil, and stir for 1 minute. Pour over warm cake.